HEADWORD: Antispastic
<hw>An`ti*spas"tic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/. See
<er>Antispast</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Believed
to cause a revulsion of fluids or of humors from one part to
another.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Counteracting
spasms; antispasmodic.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>An antispastic
agent.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
